results.name: Number of benzenoids with 21 hexagons, C_(3h) symmetry and containing n carbon atoms.
reference: G. Brinkmann, G. Caporossi and P. Hansen, "A survey and new results on computer enumeration of polyhex and fusene hydrocarbons", J. Chem. Inf. Comput. Sci., vol. 43 (2003) pp. 842-851. See Table 4 column 4 on page 846.
example: If n=61 then the number of benzenoids with 21 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 2.
If n=64 then the number of benzenoids with 21 hexagons with C_(3h) symmetry is 4.
results.author: _Parthasarathy Nambi_, Sep 24 2006
